      <hedline>
        <hl1>My County Executive Speaks for Me</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Donna Colleluori letter disputes June 3 editorial on Suffolk County Executive Steve Levy's 'dogged populism'</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As the proud granddaughter of legal immigrants to this country, one from Brazil and one from Italy, I'm offended by the June 3 editorial ''Republicrats of Long Island.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As the proud granddaughter of legal immigrants to this country, one from Brazil and one from Italy, I'm offended by the June 3 editorial ''Republicrats of Long Island.''</p>
        <p>To pigeonhole the opinions of Steve Levy, the Suffolk County executive, as ''dogged populism'' is insulting to those of us who adhere to his brand of politics. Who doesn't want government to be tough on unfair taxes, excessive spending and illegal immigrants -- not ''Latino immigrants''?</p>
        <p>Donna Colleluori  South Hempstead</p>
      </block>
